      <abstract>
        <p>Novel 1-phenyl-piperazine-2,6-diones were prepared by a new facile synthetic route using methyl <italic>N</italic>-substituted iminomonoacetate as starting material. The structures of these compounds were established by <sup>1</sup>H-NMR, <sup>13</sup>C-NMR and GC/MS. 2-(4-Chloro-5-cyclo-pentyl-oxy-2-fluorophenyl)-tetrahydro-2<italic>H</italic>-pyrido-[1,2-a]-pyrazine-1,3-(4<italic>H</italic>,6<italic>H</italic>)-dione displayed the greatest herbicidal activity.</p>
      </abstract>
