      <sec>
        <title>Herbicidal activity evaluation</title>
        <p>Three broadleaf plant species: marigold (<italic>Tagetes</italic> <italic>spp</italic>), tomato (<italic>Lycopersicon esculentus</italic>), and velvetleaf (<italic>Abutilon theophrasti</italic>) were used for the test. The seeds were allowed to germinate and grow for 14 days. Test plants were selected for uniformity, size and stage of development and then treated with the test compound, returned to the greenhouse and watered. Plants not treated with the compound under evaluation were used as a comparison. The compound to be evaluated was dissolved in acetone and sprayed using a carrier volume equivalent to 187 liters per hectare at 1200g/ha. Two weeks after application of the test compounds, the state of the plants was observed. Each species was evaluated on a scale of 0-100 in which 0 equals no activity and 100 equals total control.</p>
